For more information about EnviroAtlas data, go to https://www.epa.gov/enviroatlas/enviroatlas-fact-sheets.

			Stream length is based on the high-resolution NHD flowlines. The feature types STREAM/RIVER, CANAL/DITCH, and CONNECTOR were included; ARTIFICIAL PATH was included only where the path has a corresponding NHDArea feature with FTYPE StreamRiver. The feature types COASTLINE, PIPELINE, and UNDERGROUND CONDUIT were excluded. 
			
			Waterbody area is based on the high-resolution NHD waterbodies. All waterbody feature types were included. 
			
The impairment parent causes were grouped into the following categories:
*	Temperature: TEMPERATURE;
*	Sediment and Turbidity: SEDIMENT, TURBIDITY;
*	Biota: CAUSE UNKNOWN - FISH KILLS, CAUSE UNKNOWN - IMPAIRED BIOTA, FISH CONSUMPTION ADVISORY;
*	Mercury: MERCURY;
*	Metals other than mercury: METALS (OTHER THAN MERCURY);
*	Nuisance species: ALGAL GROWTH, NOXIOUS AQUATIC PLANTS, NUISANCE EXOTIC SPECIES, NUISANCE NATIVE SPECIES;
*	Nutrients: NUTRIENTS;
*	OrganicEnrichO2Deplet: ORGANIC ENRICHMENT/OXYGEN DEPLETION;
*	Pathogens: PATHOGENS;
*	Pesticides: PESTICIDES;
*	pH: PH/ACIDITY/CAUSTIC CONDITIONS;
*	Other: CAUSE UNKNOWN, OTHER CAUSE, FLOW ALTERATION(S), HABITAT ALTERATIONS, AMMONIA, BIOTOXINS, CHLORINE, DIOXINS, OIL AND GREASE, POLYCHLORINATED BIPHENYLS (PCBS), RADIATION, SALINITY/TOTAL DISSOLVED SOLIDS/CHLORIDES/SULFATES, TASTE, COLOR, AND ODOR, TOTAL TOXICS, TOXIC INORGANICS, TOXIC ORGANICS, TRASH
*	Total impairments: All causes

No feature types were removed from the impaired waters database; a small fraction of the impairments are for coastlines or pipelines.

For more information about EnviroAtlas data, go to https://www.epa.gov/enviroatlas/enviroatlas-fact-sheets."
